3,000 people here right now.

536
00:27:14,216 --> 00:27:18,252
The slots are what allowed the Apple II
to run, for just one example, VisiCalc,

537
00:27:18,253 --> 00:27:22,356
which from my guess single-handedly sold
between 200,000 and 300,000 machines.

538
00:27:22,357 --> 00:27:25,325
- They want slots.
- They don't get a vote.

539
00:27:25,326 --> 00:27:28,862
When Dylan wrote "Shelter from the Storm," he
didn't ask people to contribute to the lyrics.

540
00:27:28,863 --> 00:27:30,864
Plays don't stop so the
playwright can ask the audience

541
00:27:30,865 --> 00:27:32,233
what scene they'd like to see next.

542
00:27:32,234 --> 00:27:33,200
- Painters...
- Hobbyists...

543
00:27:33,201 --> 00:27:36,870
We're on the verge of
a tectonic... Hobbyists?

544
00:27:36,871 --> 00:27:38,806
A printer and a modem. Two slots.

545
00:27:40,108 --> 00:27:42,008
The Apple II team has my affection,

546
00:27:42,009 --> 00:27:45,478
but I'm not loving up a seven-year-old
product at the Mac launch.

547
00:27:45,479 --> 00:27:48,882
- Computers aren't paintings.
- Fuck you.

548
00:27:48,883 --> 00:27:52,285
I'm gonna say "fuck you" every time you
say that until you either die or stop.

549
00:27:52,286 --> 00:27:53,987
- Steve...
- Try it.

550
00:27:53,988 --> 00:27:55,121
- Steve.
- Say it.

551
00:27:55,122 --> 00:27:57,925
- Computers aren't paintings.
- Fuck you.

552
00:27:57,926 --> 00:28:00,995
Yes, they are, and what
I want is a closed system.

553
00:28:00,996 --> 00:28:05,100
End-to-end control. Completely
incompatible with anything.

554
00:28:09,137 --> 00:28:11,572
Computers aren't supposed
to have human flaws.

555
00:28:11,573 --> 00:28:15,009
I'm not going to build this one with yours.

556
00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:27,553
(both) Steve!

557
00:28:27,554 --> 00:28:28,589
Hey.

558
00:28:28,590 --> 00:28:32,225
Today is about the Macintosh.
And the Mac is mine.

559
00:28:32,226 --> 00:28:33,994
- I give you that.
- Thank you.

560
00:28:33,995 --> 00:28:36,397
I give you that. Just publicly
acknowledge the Apple II team

561
00:28:36,398 --> 00:28:37,831
'cause it's the right thing to do.

562
00:28:37,832 --> 00:28:41,467
We'll know soon enough if you are
Leonardo da Vinci or just think you are,

563
00:28:41,468 --> 00:28:43,236
but in the meantime, it would be great...

564
00:28:43,237 --> 00:28:46,139
In the meantime, the Apple II is done.

565
00:28:46,140 --> 00:28:48,207
Seven years. It was a great run.

566
00:28:48,208 --> 00:28:50,746
You should go out in the
house and take your seat.

567
00:28:52,647 --> 00:28:55,448
The Mac is Jef Raskin's.

568
00:28:55,449 --> 00:28:57,051
Say it for me.

569
00:28:57,052 --> 00:28:58,518
- Computers aren't...
- Fuck you.

570
00:28:58,519 --> 00:29:00,486
All right.

571
00:29:00,487 --> 00:29:02,757
(chattering)

572
00:29:05,126 --> 00:29:07,062
Five, six...

573
00:29:08,362 --> 00:29:10,097
- We're there?
- I need more time.

574
00:29:10,098 --> 00:29:12,131
- You can't have it.
- 20 minutes.

